WEBVTT

00:01:26.842 --> 00:01:30.153
that floods the body with several 
different stress hormones,

00:01:30.153 --> 00:01:34.580
causing physiological changes 
that prepare the body to defend itself.

00:01:34.580 --> 00:01:36.156
Our heart rate speeds up,

00:01:36.156 --> 00:01:37.163
breathing quickens,

00:01:37.163 --> 00:01:39.470
and muscles tense.

00:01:39.470 --> 00:01:41.110
Even after a crisis is over,

00:01:41.110 --> 00:01:44.629
escalated levels of stress hormones 
may last for days,

00:01:44.629 --> 00:01:46.215
contributing to jittery feelings,

00:01:46.215 --> 00:01:47.037
nightmares,

00:01:47.037 --> 00:01:48.619
and other symptoms.

00:01:48.619 --> 00:01:53.182
For most people, these experiences
disappear within a few days to two weeks

00:01:53.182 --> 00:01:55.216
as their hormone levels stabilize.

00:01:55.216 --> 00:01:58.063
But a small percentage of those
who experience trauma

